<h1>RDF Parser</h1>
<p><span property="doap:description"><a href="http://www.w3.org/RDF/">Resource Description Framework (RDF)</a> is a language for representing information about resources in the World Wide Web. The underlying abstract representation is <a href="http://w3.org/RDF">RDF</a>, which lets publishers build their own vocabulary, extend others, and evolve their vocabulary with maximal interoperability over time. RdfContext is a <span property="doap:programming-language">Ruby</span> Gem implementing RDF graphs, parsers and serializers to help integrate semantic technologies into Ruby projects.</span></p>
<p>The distiller parses RDF/XML, RDFa and N3 syntaxes to and generates output either as RDF/XML or N-Triples (N3). The <a href="#distiller">form below</a> can be used to start the service installed at this site.</p>
<p>To learn more about RDFa, please consult the <a rel="rdfs:seeAlso" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/rdfa-syntax">RDFa Syntax Document</a>. See also <a href="#distribution">below</a> for the possibilities to download the package.</p>
<p>RdfContext is a Ruby Gem implementation of <span property="doap:implements">RDF</span> including N3, RDF/XML and RDFa parsers. It is available for download and integration as open-source. The distiller runs version <%= RdfContext::VERSION %> of the gem.</p>
<h3 id="distiller">The Distiller Form</h3>
<% form_tag root_url do -%>
  <% field_set_tag("Distill RDF Information") do %>
    <p>
      <label for="uri">URI</label>
      <%= text_field_tag(:uri, @uri, :size => 80, :label => "URI") %>
      <% field_set_tag("Options") do %>
        <label for="in">Input Format:</label>
        <%= select_tag :in, options_for_select({"rdfa" => "rdfa", "rdf/xml" => "rdfxml", "N3" => "n3"}, @in) %>
        <label for="fmt">Output Format:</label>
        <%= select_tag :fmt, options_for_select({"rdf/xml" => "xml", "N Triples" => "nt"}, @fmt) %>
        <label for="debug">Show Parser debug information:</label>
        <%= check_box_tag :debug, "true", @parser_debug %>
      <% end %>
      <%= submit_tag("Submit") %>
    </p>
    <p class="help">
      To distill the RDF content of a file, give the address (URI) of a file containing RDF markup and choose the output format of the result.
    </p>
    <p class="help">
      Alternatively, you can add a full content into the text area below; <em>this will supersede any URI that you give in the field above.</em>
    </p>
    <%= text_area_tag(:content, @content, :rows => 15, :cols => 90) %>
  <% end -%>
<% end -%>
<% if @errors -%>
  <h1>Errors</h1>
  <p><%= @errors %></p>
<% elsif @parser && @parser.graph -%>
  <h1>Result</h1>
  <p>
    <%= text_area_tag(:result, @parser.graph.send(@fmt == "nt" ? :to_ntriples : :to_rdfxml), :rows => 10, :cols => 120) %>
  </p>
<% elsif @parser -%>
  <h1>Inspect</h1>
  <%= debug @parser %>
<% end -%>
<% if @parser_debug && @parser.debug %>
  <h1>Parser Debug Information:</h1>
  <pre><%= @parser.debug.join("\n") %></pre>
<% end %>
<h3>Distiller options</h3>
<dl>
  <dt>Input format (option: "in", values: "rdfxml", "rdfa", "n3")</dt>
  <dd>The default input format is RDFa</dd>
  <dt>Output format (option: "format", values: "xml", "nt")</dt>
  <dd>The default output format is N-Triples</dd>
</dl>
<h2>Alternative access to the Distiller</h2>
<p>The distiller URI may be used directly with an HTML GET by passing the source URI and fmt options as parameters:</p>
<pre>
  <%=
    url = index_url(:format => "#{@fmt}", :in => "#{@in}") + "&uri=#{h(@uri || "http://www.example.com/rdfa.html")}"
    link_to(url, url)
  %>
</pre>
